main event: A sighting was reported on November 6, 1967, in Dayton, Ohio, by two witnesses who observed an unidentified flying object.
interesting points: The sighting was categorized as insufficient data and had no confirmed physical evidence,The witnesses submitted a form but it was not returned,The observation was classified as ground-visual and lasted between 5-7 minutes, The report indicates that the observers may have seen a star-like object moving in the sky, There is a reference to both oral and diagrammatic reporting procedures.
witness description: The witnesses were likely in different locations with one being near an airfield.
